value.title: Deep in Trump country, Nevada's first openly gay, Latino mayor leads a blue-leaning city
value.excerpt: It just goes to show you that rural America and rural Nevada aren’t just monoliths," said Daniel Corona, mayor of West Wendover.

value.title: Former top cybersecurity official says Trump firing by tweet was 'not how I wanted to go out'
value.excerpt: Christopher Krebs, the former top cybersecurity official, said President Donald Trump's decision to unceremoniously fire him via tweet last week was "not how I wanted to go out."

value.title: Biden picks up small number of votes in Milwaukee County after Trump-requested recount
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden saw a small net gain in votes as Milwaukee County, Wisconsin's largest, certified its presidential general election results Friday after a recount requested by the Trump campaign.

value.title: Kamala Harris called a nurse on Thanksgiving to thank her for fighting on the Covid frontlines
value.excerpt: A friendly phone call is all too normal during Thanksgiving -- that is unless it's coming from the vice president-elect, herself.

value.title: Federal appeals court denies Trump campaign effort to revive Pennsylvania lawsuit saying 'claims have no merit'
value.excerpt: A federal appeals court denied the Trump campaign's effort to revive a federal lawsuit challenging the election results in Pennsylvania, ruling "the claims have no merit."

value.title: Trump says he'll travel to Georgia to support Republican Senate candidates in runoff election
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump said Thursday he will travel to Georgia to support the state's Republican Senate candidates ahead of the January 5 runoff election.

value.title: Joe and Jill Biden: Our most important Thanksgiving tradition
value.excerpt: This Thanksgiving, tables throughout our country will have an empty chair.

value.title: Flournoy gets progressive boost in Biden's search for Pentagon chief
value.excerpt: "We believe Michèle Flournoy is the best candidate for the job," a group of arms control veterans write in an open letter to Biden.

value.title: Chinese leader Xi Jinping congratulates Biden on winning election
value.excerpt: Chinese President Xi Jinping on Wednesday sent a congratulatory message to President-elect Joe Biden, more than two weeks after the Democratic candidate was projected the winner of the US presidential election.

value.title: Chalian on Biden's agenda: 'America First' is gone
value.excerpt: CNN's David Chalian explains how President-elect Joe Biden's approach to selecting his cabinet differs from President Trump's.

value.title: CDC ready for Biden transition: "This is what we've been waiting for"
value.excerpt: Leadership at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, beset by a Trump White House that was harshly critical of the agency's coronavirus response, are anticipating the Biden transition team and the change a new administration will bring, senior health officials tell CNN.

value.title: Can Manny Diaz resurrect Democrats? — Poll: Majority of GOP would support Trump in 2024 — Florida tops 18,000 Covid-19 deaths
value.excerpt: Is this the answer that Florida Democrats have been hoping for? Jumping into the fray — Former Miami Mayor Manny Diaz, who earned a reputation as a turnaround artist in his home city, is campaigning for an even tougher job: leading the floundering Florida Democratic Party.

value.title: Virginia Democrats, Thrilled With Biden Victory, Aren’t Looking for Carbon Copy
value.excerpt: Suburban women who played a huge role in Joe Biden’s victory are not convinced that they need a white man to win their governor’s race next year.

value.title: Keilar calls Sydney Powell a Trump 'scapegoat'
value.excerpt: CNN's Brianna Keilar takes a look at Trump's legal team distancing itself from Sydney Powell, a lawyer who spoke at the campaign's press conference laying out its case for widespread voter fraud.

value.title: Biden poised to nominate Antony Blinken as secretary of state
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is poised to nominate Antony Blinken to serve as secretary of state, people familiar with the matter told CNN, elevating a longtime foreign policy adviser as Biden makes his first round of Cabinet announcements Tuesday.

value.title: Chris Christie calls Trump's legal team a 'national embarrassment'
value.excerpt: A staunch ally of Donald Trump said Sunday it was time for the President to end his futile gambit to overturn the results of the election.

value.title: Trump rails against Paris climate accord in virtual G20 event
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump railed against the Paris climate accord and touted American oil and natural gas production during a virtual session focused on safeguarding the environment on the final day of the Group of 20 summit.

value.title: Joe Biden's Irish ancestral hometown, Ballina, revels in win as London grows uneasy over Brexit
value.excerpt: Ballina, once known as the salmon fishing capital of Ireland, now boasts its very own incoming American president.

value.title: Trump digs deeper into debunked conspiracy theories instead of embracing reality
value.excerpt: At first, President Donald Trump's refusal to concede an election he clearly lost appeared to many of his allies a temporary stage of grief. Give it a few days, some shrugged. A week, tops.

value.title: Mitt Romney calls Trump's attempt to overturn Michigan election 'undemocratic'
value.excerpt: Two prominent Republican senators on Thursday ripped President Donald Trump's attempt to overturn the results of the presidential election in Michigan, with one going so far as to call the President's strategy "undemocratic."

value.title: Trump's refusal to concede creates strange gap between Biden and Harris on classified intelligence
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris took part in a classified briefing of the Senate Intelligence Committee this week and emerged in a strange position -- being more informed about current threats than President-elect Joe Biden but bound by congressional rules to keep that information from him.

value.title: Washington Post: Trump spoke to GOP official who now wants to 'rescind' vote to certify Detroit's results
value.excerpt: The two Republican members of the Wayne County Board of Canvassers want to "rescind" their votes to certify the presidential results from the county, the largest in Michigan and home to the city of Detroit, even though the board has already certified the results.

value.title: Former GSA administrator: 'It's clear' we should recognize Biden as the President-elect
value.excerpt: The former head of the General Services Administration during the 2000 election said Thursday that he would ascertain the 2020 results and begin the formal transition to a Joe Biden presidency, which the current administrator has yet to do.

value.title: Working for Trump Ends in Getting Fired or Getting Covid, Kimmel Says
value.excerpt: President Trump fired Christopher Krebs, a senior cybersecurity official, via Twitter on Tuesday. “Usually to get rid of Krebs, Trump uses a little comb and some medicated shampoo,” Jimmy Kimmel joked.

value.title: Joe Biden, nurse share emotional moment during virtual roundtable
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden grew emotional during a virtual roundtable after hearing Mary Turner, an intensive care unit nurse, describe her experience on the frontline battling Covid-19. The Minnesota nurse spoke with CNN's Erin Burnett.

value.title: Biden acknowledges 'real brick walls' he'll face in Senate during video call with supporters
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden acknowledged in a private video call with supporters on Wednesday that he will face "real brick walls" in the Senate if Republicans maintain their majority but said he thinks he can overcome the political divides that may exist.

value.title: Trump's legal adviser Jenna Ellis in 2016 called him an 'idiot' and said his supporters didn't care about 'facts or logic'
value.excerpt: Jenna Ellis has been one of President Donald Trump's most ardent defenders since joining his campaign as a legal adviser and surrogate a year ago, but in early 2016 she was one of his toughest critics and deeply opposed his candidacy, according to a CNN KFile review of statements she made on her official

value.title: Kevin McCarthy, the House Minority Leader, Doesn’t Think Trump Is Going Away
value.excerpt: The California Republican believes his party’s victories in 2020 came thanks to the president, not in spite of him: “He brought turnout.”

value.title: 'Just ridiculous': CNN speaks to Georgia voter the Trump campaign falsely accused of casting ballot in the name of a dead woman
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's campaign and Fox News host Tucker Carlson alleged last week that a vote cast by a Georgia woman named Deborah Jean Christiansen was fraudulent.

value.title: Trump lashes out in new bid to tarnish an election he lost
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump flexed the power of his office Tuesday to tarnish America's free and fair election, sacking the official who declared the vote the most secure in US history, even as more of his false claims of massive fraud were exposed as baseless in court.
